36#include "krb5_locl.h"
37
38KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
39krb5_build_ap_req (krb5_context context,
40 krb5_enctype enctype,
41 krb5_creds *cred,
42 krb5_flags ap_options,
43 krb5_data authenticator,
44 krb5_data *retdata)
45{
46 krb5_error_code ret = 0;
47 AP_REQ ap;
48 Ticket t;
49 size_t len;
50
51 ap.pvno = 5;
52 ap.msg_type = krb_ap_req;
53 memset(&ap.ap_options, 0, sizeof(ap.ap_options));
54 ap.ap_options.use_session_key = (ap_options & AP_OPTS_USE_SESSION_KEY) > 0;
55 ap.ap_options.mutual_required = (ap_options & AP_OPTS_MUTUAL_REQUIRED) > 0;
56
57 ap.ticket.tkt_vno = 5;
58 copy_Realm(&cred->server->realm, &ap.ticket.realm);
59 copy_PrincipalName(&cred->server->name, &ap.ticket.sname);
60
61 decode_Ticket(cred->ticket.data, cred->ticket.length, &t, &len);
62 copy_EncryptedData(&t.enc_part, &ap.ticket.enc_part);
63 free_Ticket(&t);
64
65 ap.authenticator.etype = enctype;
66 ap.authenticator.kvno = NULL;
67 ap.authenticator.cipher = authenticator;
68
69 ASN1_MALLOC_ENCODE(AP_REQ, retdata->data, retdata->length,
70 &ap, &len, ret);
71 if(ret == 0 && retdata->length != len)
72 krb5_abortx(context, "internal error in ASN.1 encoder");
73 free_AP_REQ(&ap);
74 return ret;
75
76}
